<br>
If you keep your tailoring level around or just below (like me) what it needs to be to make your own armor, you won't be making that much money.  The money you could make out hunting is probably comparable.  You might make a little more money tailoring, but you're not getting exp by tailoring, either.  However, if you raise your tailoring above your level, e.g. a 400 skill 10th level tailor, you will make tons of money beyond what your level could get hunting.<br>
<br>
